This paper proposes a method to improve the gradient estimation of Evolutionary Strategies (ES) in deep neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning and optimization. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on MNIST and reinforcement learning tasks, which are common benchmarks in the field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.RO (Robotics).
